    "content": "<p>The reagent which can do the conversion $$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{OH}$$ is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4$$/ ether\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{H}_2, \\mathrm{Pt}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{Na}$$ and $$\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4$$/ether is an reducing agent, thus it can reduces carboxylic acid (in this case is acetic acid) to alcohols (in this case is ethanol). The overall reaction is as follows</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4 / \\text { ether }} \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$$</p>",
