    "explanation": "<p>The given reaction take place in following way</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbqy9je/a030266b-15e5-4757-b80c-e4141d3519e0/e953b2a0-d97d-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbqy9jf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbqy9je/a030266b-15e5-4757-b80c-e4141d3519e0/e953b2a0-d97d-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbqy9jf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 7 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Phenol gives white ppt. with bromine water.</p>\n<p>Acetone when treated with $$\\mathrm{Ba}(\\mathrm{OH})_2$$ undergoes aldol condensation as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbqzza6/e9dbc1d6-44e8-4336-a3fa-9309d61df827/1905eef0-d97e-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbqzza7.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbqzza6/e9dbc1d6-44e8-4336-a3fa-9309d61df827/1905eef0-d97e-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbqzza7.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 7 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>On heating further, ketol gives 4-methylpent-3-en-2-one</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbr1llw/1e151cff-db5f-469e-a7d2-463774c78189/4613e640-d97e-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbr1llx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbr1llw/1e151cff-db5f-469e-a7d2-463774c78189/4613e640-d97e-11ee-8474-a73dd823a51b/file-1ltbr1llx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 7 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ The product D is 4-methylpent-3-en-2-one.</p>",
