    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Propanoic acid undergoes HVZ reaction to give chloropropanoic acid. The product obtained is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "stronger acid than propanoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "as stronger as propanoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "weaker acid than propanoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "stronger than dichloropropanoic acid"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Propanoic acid undergoes $$\\mathrm{HVZ}$$ reaction to give chloropropanoic acid. The product obtained is stronger acid than propanoic acid because chloropropanoic acid contain EWG. (Cl-group) that increases the stability of the carboxylate ion by dispersing the negative charge.</p>\n<p>Reaction involved is as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltspl7in/38dc8287-c4a9-4db2-80c9-e8dd059eab90/e8286df0-e2d1-11ee-bcee-05b9fbe191e5/file-1ltspl7io.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltspl7in/38dc8287-c4a9-4db2-80c9-e8dd059eab90/e8286df0-e2d1-11ee-bcee-05b9fbe191e5/file-1ltspl7io.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2019 Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 5 English Explanation\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2019,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2019",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>$$P \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}_2 / \\text { Pd- } \\mathrm{BaSO}_4} Q \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii)Dil. } \\mathrm{HCl}]{\\text { (i) Con. } \\mathrm{NaOH}}$$</p>\n<p>$$R$$ and $$S$$ form benzyl benzoate when treated with each other. Hence $$P$$ is</p>",
