        "content": "$$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{COOH}$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In the given reaction, $$P$$ is benzoyl chloride, $$Q$$ is benzaldehyde, $$R$$ is benzylalcohol and $$S$$ is benzoic acid.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltspur9f/47c4d20e-264f-4adb-af30-785a8f1414ba/f1b11d30-e2d2-11ee-bcee-05b9fbe191e5/file-1ltspur9g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltspur9f/47c4d20e-264f-4adb-af30-785a8f1414ba/f1b11d30-e2d2-11ee-bcee-05b9fbe191e5/file-1ltspur9g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2019 Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English Explanation\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
